# Rendering Pipeline

## Pass Order (per frame)

```
Shadow pass   → shadowFbo (2048² depth)
Forward pass  → MSAA sceneFbo (lit + skinned, opaque sorted, transparent back-to-front)
MSAA resolve  → sceneFbo.colorTex
Post-process chain (ping-pong) → screen
```

## Post-Process Chain

Stages execute in insertion order via `RenderPipeline.addPostProcess(stage)`.
Each stage receives the previous stage's output texture; the last writes to screen.

```typescript
const myStage: PostProcessStage = {
  name: 'bloom',
  enabled: true,
  draw: (inputTex, w, h, outputFbo) => bloomPass.draw(inputTex, w, h, outputFbo),
};
pipeline.addPostProcess(myStage);
```

Built-in engine stage:
1. `tone-color` — ACES tone-map + warm grade + cheap bloom (always on)

Optional stages (registered by the game):
- `ascii` — via `createAsciiPostProcessStage(gl)`; game owns toggle input

## Adding a New Pass

- Create `viberanium/src/render/passes/myPass.ts` — a small class with a `draw(...)` method matching the `PostProcessStage` interface.
- Create shaders in `viberanium/src/render/shaders/my.ts` and wire via a factory or `pipeline.addPostProcess`.
- Games register optional stages from `bootstrap.ts`.

## Shader Conventions

- Every shader file exports only GLSL strings (template literals, no runtime logic)
- Shared GLSL (e.g. shadow sampling) is imported as a const string and interpolated: `${shadowSamplingGLSL}`
- `fullscreenVS` in `shaders/post.ts` is the canonical full-screen triangle VS — reuse it for all post passes

## Draw collection

The render pipeline collects draw items from:

1. `meshDraws.parts[]` on any entity (skeletal characters, bone-attachment children)
2. `renderable` on simple entities (static prop sub-entities, legacy paths)
3. `groundPlane` on the scene ground entity (drawn with the dedicated ground shader)

Each `MeshDrawPart` supplies `mesh`, `material`, `model` (world matrix), optional `skin`, and `visible`/`castShadow` flags. Pose and attachment systems write `part.model` each frame before draw order 0 runs.

Runtime visibility: set `part.visible = false` or `renderable.visible = false`. Runtime material swap: replace `part.material` or `material.baseColorTex`.

Draw collection also applies distance cull (`forwardCullDist` / `shadowCullDist`) and CPU sphere-vs-frustum cull using each mesh's precomputed `boundsCenter` / `boundsRadius`. Camera frustum cull only skips the forward pass. Shadow casters are culled against the light frustum (and `shadowCullDist`) so off-screen objects can still cast into view without filling the shadow pass with casters outside the shadow map. Backface culling is on by default; set `material.doubleSided = true` (or glTF `doubleSided`) to disable it per draw. Ground draws always disable cull.

`ForwardPass` tracks `lastProgram / lastTex / lastVao` to skip redundant GL state changes.
Opaque items are sorted by `(skinPalette, baseColorTex, vao, distance)` so shared joint palettes upload once per batch.
Transparent items are sorted back-to-front by camera distance.
